1604898000.title: Bargain Hunt
1604898000.descr: Two teams of amateur antique collectors meet at an antiques fair to compete to make the largest profit from a three hundred pound budget. Once the contestants have done the shopping for their own items, the experts then take any leftover money and go shopping for more antiques which is 'bonus buys'. The teams then have to decide whether or not to take these items to auction.

1604900700.title: Bargain Hunt
1604900700.descr: Natasha Raskin Sharp is in charge today as Bargain Hunt visits the Westpoint Arena near Exeter. Two sisters take on husband and wife as they race against the clock to buy three items in 60 minutes, with Danny Sebastian and Gary Pe keeping the red and blue teams on track. Meanwhile, Natasha learns about a mysterious book from the Far East.

1604903400.title: Father Brown
1604903400.descr: Father Brown is a Catholic priest and an amateur detective solving murder cases, set during the 1950s in the fictional village Kembleford in Cotswold area, England. He uses his own wits as well as skills of his close friends, and being a priest allows him to look straight to the truth. He is strongly against the capital punishment for the capital crimes, as still applied in Britain of that time.

1604906100.title: Call the Midwife
1604906100.descr: Christmas is coming, and in Poplar the midwives of Nonnatus House are busier than ever. When an abandoned baby is discovered on the steps of the convent, the whole community rallies round to try to find its mother.

1604908800.title: Call the Midwife
1604908800.descr: Period drama series set in East London in the 1950s, following the life and work of a young midwife Jenny Lee and her colleagues at the Nonnatus House nursing convent. They serve the poor society of Poplar, London. Their main duty is to help bring safe birth to women and help them look after their newborns.

1604925000.title: Still Open All Hours

It follows Granville who has now taken charge of the Arkwright's shop after the sad death of his uncle. A funny insight into the life of Granville who is following his late uncle's old ways with his unique selling techniques. British comedy.

1604926800.title: Impossible
1604926800.descr: Entertaining and educational British quiz show, hosted by Rick Edwards, where 24 regular contestants compete throughout the series to answer tricky questions. But some of the optional answers are designed to be ''impossible'', or at the very least inconsistent with the information given. The participants must avoid selecting these booby trap answer and the best one wins the £10,000 jackpot.

1604950500.title: EastEnders
1604950500.descr: Albert Square, a traditional Victorian square of terrace houses surrounding a park in the East End is home to many families and is a place where romance, jealousy, domestic rivalry, gossip and extramarital affairs are regularly featured. This "slice of life" series, broadcasted since 1985, follows the stories of local residents and their families and their dilemmas.

1604954700.title: Shakespeare & Hathaway: Private Investigators
1604954700.descr: Strife in Stratford-upon-Avon calls for the minds of the best criminal detectives in the West Midlands. Ex-detective inspector, Frank Hathaway is now a private investigator, flooded by debts. When he's called on by Luella Shakespeare, a suspicious woman wanting to look into the doings of her fiance, Hathaway and Shakespeare get thrown together in an investigation of the highest degree... murder.

1604957400.title: Bad Move
1604957400.descr: Steve (Jack Dee) and Nicky (Kerry Godliman) decide to move from Leeds to the countryside of Yorkshire, where they want to live a perfect, simple life away from the rat race. Soon they find out that the reality is more than disappointing. The house is in a bad condition, the internet doesn't reach, they miss many amenities of every day life. And the neighbours can be really annoying.

1604958900.title: Scott & Bailey
1604958900.descr: Follow personal and professional lives of Detectives Janet Scott and Rachel Bailey, members of the Major Incident Team- MIT, within the fictional Manchester Metropolitan Police who solve difficult cases and fight crime whilst risking their lives on a daily basis in order to help those in need.

1604961600.title: Rillington Place
1604961600.descr: The shocking true story of the serial killer John Christie is retold in this compelling three-part drama series. Directed by Craig Viveiros, the series chronicles the life of Christie, beginning with the break out of WWII and up to his execution, revealing the toxic marriage with his wife Ethel and the relationship he had with neighbour Timothy Evans. Featuring performances from Tim Roth, Nico Mirallegro, Samantha Morton, Jodie Comer and Eiry Thomas.
